articles.title: Yahoo Finance
articles.content: Real Estate Investment Trusts (REITs) have long been a favourite among Singapore investors. They are prized for their steady dividends and relatively low volatility compared to individual stocks. But not everything you hear about REITs is true. Not understanding how REITs work or believing common myths can lead to poor investment decisions and disappointing returns. Follow as we bust three common REIT myths and show why careful selection and a long-term mindset matter more than chasing short-term yields. It is only human to chase after the highest yields, believing that more income is always better. Understanding how yields work is crucial. A REITâ€™s yield is calculated by dividing annual distribution per unit by the unit price. Unfortunately, itâ€™s usually the latter.

articles.title: Hundreds feared dead after migrant boat capsizes off Malaysia
articles.content: Hundreds of people are feared dead after a migrant boat from Myanmar capsized near Malaysia. At least seven bodies have been found and 13 people rescued after 300 people failed to arrive in Malaysia having left Myanmarâ€™s Rakhine state. Officials believe the passengers boarded a large ship and were then placed into three smaller boats, to evade detection as they approached the Malaysian coast. The remaining six bodies were discovered on Sunday before the operation was suspended. It was scheduled to resume on Monday.
